HEADWORD: Embogue
<hw>Em*bogue"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Disembogue</er>.]</ety> <def>To disembogue; to discharge, as a
river, its waters into the sea or another river.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

